wikipedia_page.main: Ann Muriel, Lady Gammans (née Paul; 6 March 1898 – 28 December 1989) was a British Conservative politician. She was elected Member of Parliament for Hornsey at a 1957 by-election following the death of her husband Sir David Gammans, and served until her retirement at the 1966 general election.
